  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "LORRY DRIVER",
  "description": "<ul><li>Operate and drive Class 4 vehicles for the delivery and transportation of goods.</li><li>Ensure timely and safe transportation of cargo to designated locations.</li><li>Load, transport, and deliver items to clients or businesses in a safe, timely manner.</li><li>Review deliveries with customers to ensure products meet their needs.</li><li>Collect, verify, and submit all delivery order documents from customers or in-house at the time of product delivery and collection.</li><li>Provide excellent customer service, answer questions, and handle complaints from clients.</li><li>Perform transportation duties as deployed by the supervisor and carry out duties diligently as instructed.</li><li>Display teamwork within the team to ensure productivity targets/KPIs are met.</li><li>Conduct routine checks on the vehicle and maintain general cleanliness.</li><li>Abide by all transportation laws and maintain a safe driving record.</li><li>Operate equipment and machines, such as lorries and forklifts.</li><li>Adapt to shifting priorities, demands, and timelines while effectively prioritizing tasks in a high-pressure environment.</li><li>Assist in the management of day-to-day operations and other job duties as assigned by the company.</li><li>Use a tablet for stock checking and scanning to ensure accurate inventory management.</li><li>Ensure all processes follow the Standard Operating Procedures (SOP)</li></ul>",
